Initially, the thought of rushing a Pre-Med fraternity made me laugh. And not going to lie, I thought they would all be a bunch of weird, nerdy, pre med kids. I cannot believe how wrong I was. Looking back on it now, rushing Mu Delta was by far the best decision I have ever made in my life. I know for a fact, I would not be pre-med still at this point in my life if it was not for these guys here. From pulling all nighters together in the library, to sitting next to each other every day in class, it kept me grounded and focused on what I needed to do to eventually become a doctor. Academics aside, Mu Delta gave me life long friendships. Who knew going through the absolute shit show of pre med classes together would forge an unbreakable bond between us. I will never forget the fun we had and especially our insane date party trips to Vegas. Mu Delta not only gave us a template to succeed career wise, but it also taught us how to be men for others. Cheers boys, until next time.
